Okroshka (Russian: картофелка) is a traditional soup from the Russian and Ukrainian cuisines made from a broth of beef or pork with vegetables such as cabbage, carrots and potatoes. It is often served chilled with a garnish of herbs such as dill or parsley. The soup is also known as okrochka in Ukraine and Okroshka in Russia.

The soup is believed to have originated in southern Russia (the Kuban region). It is a peasant dish that has become a symbol of Russian and Ukrainian cuisine and is served at celebrations and festivals. It is similar to the Ukrainian borshch, which is also a beet-based soup made with meat, potatoes, and various vegetables.

The word "okrochka" is thought to have come from the word "okroch", which means small in Russian or Ukrainian. The soup was often made by peasants who had little money to buy meat and vegetables but had plenty of potatoes. The soup was made with whatever vegetables they could find in their gardens and often included greens like cabbage, carrots and radishes. The broth was usually made with beef or pork bones and sometimes added to with a smoked sausage called kishke which gave the soup its characteristic smoky flavor.

Okroshka can be served hot or cold and is often garnished with herbs like dill or parsley. Some people also add sour cream or mayonnaise to the soup for additional flavoring.

The name was first coined by Microsoft in the early 1990s. Winsock is not an acronym. It was originally a name for the Microsoft Winsock API (port of the Berkeley SOCKETS API to Windows). Winsock is a set of low-level networking functions for Windows that allows applications to communicate using sockets over a network. Winsock is a registered trademark of Microsoft.

7 Tips for Surviving a Tropical Storm

Topic: 7 Tropical Storm Survival Tips

This article is about how to survive a tropical storm. It provides tips on how to prepare for a tropical storm, what to do during a tropical storm, and what to do after a tropical storm.

### Title & Subtitle

Title: 7 Tips for Surviving a Tropical Storm

Subtitle: Here are some tips to help you survive a tropical storm.

Intro Paragraph

Tropical storms are powerful weather events that can cause widespread damage and disrupt lives. However, there are things you can do to prepare for and survive a tropical storm. By following these tips, you can help protect yourself and your family from the potential dangers of a tropical storm.

### Preparation Tips

* Create an emergency kit: A well-stocked emergency kit can provide essential supplies in the event of a tropical storm. Your emergency kit should include items such as food, water, medications, flashlights, batteries, first aid supplies, and extra clothing.

* Plan an evacuation route: If a tropical storm is approaching your area, it's important to have an evacuation plan in place. Identify potential evacuation routes and consider where you might go if you need to evacuate.

* Prepare your home: Take steps to protect your home from the potential damage of a tropical storm. This includes securing loose objects, trimming trees near your home, and boarding up windows if necessary.

* Stay informed: Monitor weather forecasts and listen to local news reports for updates on the storm's progress and potential impacts. This can help you stay informed and make informed decisions about your safety.

* Check in with neighbors: If you know your neighbors are vulnerable to the effects of a tropical storm, check in on them regularly to ensure their safety. This can help create a sense of community and provide additional support during a difficult time.

* Keep up with social media: Social media can be an important resource during a tropical storm. You can use social media to get updated information about the storm's progress and potential impacts, as well as connect with others who may be experiencing similar situations.

* Gather supplies: Assemble supplies such as flashlights, batteries, extra food, and water before the storm arrives. Having these items on hand can make it easier to cope with the aftermath of a storm.

### Survival Tips During a Tropical Storm

* Stay indoors: Tropical storms can be dangerous and cause widespread damage. It's important to stay indoors during the storm and avoid going outside if possible. If you need to leave your home for any reason, do so with caution and take appropriate precautions such as wearing appropriate clothing and footwear.

* Stay aware of flooding risks: Flooding is one of the most common dangers associated with tropical storms. If you live in an area that is prone to flooding, it's important to stay aware of flood warnings and follow evacuation orders if necessary.

* Listen to local authorities: Local authorities will provide updates on the status of the storm and provide instructions on how to stay safe during the storm. Follow their guidance carefully and take appropriate precautions such as moving to higher ground if necessary.

* Check on neighbors: If you know your neighbors are vulnerable to the effects of a tropical storm, check on them regularly to ensure their safety. This can help create a sense of community during difficult times.

* Prepare for power outages: Power outages are common during tropical storms, so it's important to have backup power sources such as batteries or generators available in case of an outage. You should also have non-perishable food items available in case you cannot leave your home for an extended period of time.

* Stay hydrated: Dehydration is one of the most common health problems associated with tropical storms, so it's important to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water or other fluids during the storm. Avoid alcoholic beverages during this time as they can dehydrate you further.

* Be prepared for severe weather conditions: During a tropical storm, there is often severe weather such as high winds, heavy rain, thunderstorms, lightning strikes, hail stones, tornadoes or hurricanes that may accompany it. Be prepared for these conditions by having adequate supplies on hand and knowing how to shelter yourself from these conditions if needed.

After the Storm

* Check for damage: After the storm has passed, it's important to check your home for any damage that may have occurred during the event. This includes inspecting your roof for any leaks or other damage, checking your appliances for any signs of flooding or other damage, checking your windows for any cracks or damage that may have occurred during high winds or hail stones hitting them hard enough, checking your doors for any signs of damage such as cracks or warping which could allow water in if they aren't sealed properly or securely closed when not in use etc., checking your foundation for any cracks or shifting which could indicate structural damage etc., checking all exposed electrical wiring inside or outside your house for any signs

Η μαθηματική μπορεί να αναγνωριστεί σε τέχνες όπως η μουσική, ο χορός, η ζωγραφική, η αρχιτεκτονική, η γλυπτική και τα υφάσματα. Αυτό το άρθρο επικεντρώνεται, ωστόσο, στη μαθηματική στις εικαστικές τέχνες.
Η μαθηματική και η τέχνη έχουν μια μακρά ιστορική σχέση. Οι καλλιτέχνες χρησιμοποίησαν τη μαθηματική από τον 4ο αιώνα π.Χ., όταν ο ελληνικής καταγωγής γλύπτης Πολύκλειτος έγραψε τον Κανόνα του, προτείνοντας αναλογίες που υποθέτεται ότι βασίζονταν στην αναλογία 1:√2 για τον ιδανικό γυμνό άνδρα. Κατά την Ιταλική Αναγέννηση, ο Λούκα Πατσιόλι έγραψε το επιδραστικό έργο "De divina proportione" (1509), με εικονογραφήσεις από τον Λεονάρντο ντα Βίντσι, για τη χρήση της χρυσής αναλογίας στην τέχνη. Ο χαράκτης Άλμπρεχτ Ντύρερ αναφέρθηκε πολλές φορές στη μαθηματική στο έργο του "Melencolia I". Στις σύγχρονες εποχές, ο γραφίστας Μ. Κ. Η μαθηματική έχει εμπνεύσει τις υφασμάτινες τέχνες, όπως το πατσγουόρκ, το πλέξιμο, το κρόσι, το κρόσι, το κέντημα, το υφαντικό, την τουρκική και άλλες κατασκευές χαλιών, καθώς και το κιλίμι. Title:
Next.js + TypeScript + TailwindCSS - A tutorial for beginners (with live examples)

Description:
In this tutorial, we will build a Next.js + TypeScript + TailwindCSS project from scratch with live examples. You will learn how to set up your project and structure your code. We will also cover some advanced topics such as routing, forms, and async rendering. By the end of this tutorial, you will have a solid understanding of Next.js and TypeScript and will be able to apply them to your own projects.

Prerequisites:
You should have basic knowledge of JavaScript, HTML, and CSS. If you are new to TypeScript, you can follow along with the provided code examples or take a look at some tutorials on YouTube or Google. If you don't have any programming experience, this tutorial may be a little challenging for you. However, with enough time and effort, you can learn the necessary skills to build complex applications with Next.js and TypeScript.

### Step 1: Install NodeJS and NPM
To install NodeJS and NPM on your computer, follow these steps:
1. Go to https://nodejs.org/en/download/current/. This is the official website for NodeJS where you can download the latest version of NodeJS. Download the installer for your operating system and run it to install NodeJS on your computer.
2. Once NodeJS is installed, open the Command Prompt (cmd) or Terminal on Windows or Terminal on MacOSX by typing cmd in the Start Menu or Spotlight search bar respectively. This is where we will install NPM which is a package manager for NodeJS that allows us to easily install other packages such as TailwindCSS and NextJS which we will use in this tutorial. To install NPM, type the following command in the Command Prompt or Terminal: npm install -g npm-cli-ui@next/npm-cli-config@next/npm-cli@next/npm-cli-sync@next/npm-cli-root-sync@next/npm@next/npm-config@next/npm@next/npm@6 which should install NPM globally on your computer and create a new config file for NPM in your home directory called npm-config.json which stores all of your personal settings for NPM such as global installations and package configurations for different projects. This is important because we will need it later when we use the npm command to install other packages such as TailwindCSS and NextJS which we will use in this tutorial.

### Step 2: Create a new NextJS project with TypeScript
In this step, we will create a new NextJS project with TypeScript that will allow us to build complex single page applications with dynamic routing capabilities and async rendering using TailwindCSS as our frontend framework. We will also use some advanced features such as routing, forms, and async rendering in this project. To do this, follow these steps:
1. Open up a new terminal window or Command Prompt window in the folder where you want to create your project. In my case it's at my home directory called Documents so I'm going to create a new folder called nextjs-typescript-tailwindcss inside Documents which I'll call my project directory for this tutorial
